===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*«µ ∞elh‚ÇÉ-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|yelow|yelwe, yelou}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ƒ°eolwe}}, oblique form of {{inh|en|ang|ƒ°eolu}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*gelu}}, from  {{inh|en|gem-pro|*gelwaz}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*«µ ∞elh‚ÇÉwos}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*«µ ∞elh‚ÇÉ-||gleam, yellow}}.
Compare {{cog|cy|gwelw||pale}}, {{cog|la|helvus||dull yellow}}, {{cog|ga|geal||white, bright}}, {{cog|lt|≈æalias||green}}, {{cog|grc|œáŒªœâœÅœåœÇ||light green}}, {{cog|fa|ÿ≤ÿ±ÿØ|tr=zard||yellow}}, {{cog|sa|‡§π‡§∞‡§ø||greenish-yellow}}. Cognate with {{cog|de|gelb||yellow}}, {{cog|nl|geel||yellow}}.
The verb is from {{inh|en|ang|ƒ°eolwian}}, from the adjective.
